					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Players of <em>Smash Bros.</em> on a Nintendo 64 or GameCube controller would be used to this binding:<br /><br />A, X, Up: jump<br />B: kick<br />Y: shoot<br /><br />Players of <em>Smash Bros.</em> on a Wii Classic Controller would be used to this binding:<br /><br />Y, X, Up: jump<br />A: kick<br />B: shoot<br /><br />I guess you could subject your play testers to a &quot;config wizard&quot; like the following and see what they come up with.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Press button for<br />each action<br /><br />&gt; Jump<br />&nbsp; Kick<br />&nbsp; Fire<br /></div><br /><br />Pressing B would advance to the next line:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Press button for<br />each action<br /><br />&nbsp; Jump - B<br />&gt; Kick<br />&nbsp; Fire<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

